
Overview of verb worship

The verb worship has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (5) idolize, idolise, worship, hero-worship, revere -- (love unquestioningly and uncritically or to excess; venerate as an idol; "Many teenagers idolized the Beatles")
2. (2) worship -- (show devotion to (a deity); "Many Hindus worship Shiva")
3. (1) worship -- (attend religious services; "They worship in the traditional manner")
